Former Super Eagles captain Austin Jay Jay Okocha has hailed Taiwo Awoniyi for his performance in Nigeria’s 1-0 win over Egypt in the Group C opener of the 2021 African Cup of Nations (AFCON). Awoniyi who started the match for coach Austin Eguavoen-tutored side against the Pharaohs of Egypt described the former Golden Eaglets star as a committed player whose efforts in the match aided Nigeria’s goal in the first match. “I am particularly impressed with the commitment of Awoniyi because he was always on the neck of the Egyptian defence,” noted the former Bolton Wanderers midfielder in a post-match analysis. “His charge most times confused the defenders to make errors at the backline.   Eagles’ strategy cut off Salah, says Eguavoen     Eagles outclass Pharaohs to claim key AFCON win     AFCON: Iheanacho’s goal keeps Nigeria ahead against Egypt   “ He put in everything into the match and I think he has been able to convince me that what he has been doing in the Bundesliga was not a fluke,” he said. Okocha also have some kind words for Leicester City’s striker Kelechi Iheanacho after he was awarded the Man-of-the-Match of the encounter: - Advertisement - “Though I have my preference as the Man of the match but that goal by Kelechi deserves the man of the match because that was the goal that gave us (Nigeria) the victory. “ Overall, Okocha lauded the team for their gusty display against the Egyptians: “I think the Eagles played very well, and they were determined from the beginning of the match. They held the ball and they utilized their chances in the game. I am particularly impressed to see Eagles played well against the Egyptians,” Okocha, a guest on Supersport, added.